    {
        "user": "U066TQFTXFT",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1758760598.377339",
        "client_msg_id": "c087ffdf-681a-4b38-a9fd-bd041ed8dcb5",
        "text": "I can offer better advice if you can say more about what kinds of this you like to do in cities. But some generic \"SF tourist\" advice:\n\n• the Sutro Baths are pretty and worth a walk around\n• best secret view of the city is Tank Hill, de Young viewing tower also good, avoid Twin Peaks\n• take a Waymo, it's fun\n• avoid Fisherman's Wharf\n• Cable Car Museum is free and surprisingly neat\n• best beach is probably Baker Beach (note: nude at one end; swimming is intermittently dangerous, if you like swimming in frigid waters, go to Aquatic Park instead)\n• Dolores Park on the weekend is a scene\n• my favorite \"just wander around\" neighborhood is Mission\/Castro, although I'm biased\n• good burritos at Papalote (La Taqueria also good, get crispy tacos, but very long lines)\n• fancier vegetarian dining with nice views: <https:\/\/www.greensrestaurant.com>\n• do not leave *anything* in your car unattended, anywhere in the city, even for a short time, even hidden under a seat.\n• Dandelion Chocolate is touristy but really good chocolate. Bi-Rite Ice Cream has best ice cream around. Tartine has remarkable pastries.\nThere's plenty more where that came from. Happy to answer questions, expound more--just lmk what you want to know.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
